// Test file for Lead API endpoints
// You can use this with tools like Postman, Insomnia, or REST Client VS Code extension

### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5050/api/leads

### 1. Create a new lead
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Rahul Sharma",
  "phone": "+91 98765 43210",
  "email": "rahul@tech.com",
  "source": "Website",
  "value": 4500,
  "status": "New",
  "notes": "Interested in premium plan. Follow up on Monday."
}

###

### 2. Get all leads
GET {{baseUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 3. Get all leads with search filter
GET {{baseUrl}}?search=rahul
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4. Get all leads with status filter
GET {{baseUrl}}?status=New
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 5. Get lead by ID (replace {leadId} with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/YOUR_LEAD_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6. Update lead
PUT {{baseUrl}}/YOUR_LEAD_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "Contacted",
  "notes": "Called and discussed requirements"
}

###

### 7. Delete lead
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/YOUR_LEAD_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 8. Get lead statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 9. Get lead statistics with date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats?startDate=2024-01-01&endDate=2024-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

